sources.title: Trailing North (1933) BOB STEELE
sources.description:
First Time on YouTube!
Stars: Bob Steele, Doris Hill, George Gabby Hayes
Director: John P. McCarthy

After a daring stagecoach robbery, Ranger Jay Jones collapses in the station doorway and reports his partner Jim Powers has been shot. A rescue party, including Lee Evans, locates the fatally wounded Ranger in a cabin. As he dies, Powers tells Lee when they find a woman named Mitzi, they will find the killer.

metadata.Plot: As Powers is dying he tells Lee to look for a man with a girl named Mitzi. Heading north by dog sled as Curly the Kid, he finds her and her friend Lucky. But Flash is another friend and Lee is in trouble when his true identity becomes known.
metadata.Actors: Bob Steele, Doris Hill, Arthur Rankin
